AIM Auction Test Plan: Test Case 1:Verify that in an AIM auction PO and MO can have Order origin as C-Customer
Test Case 2:Verify that in an AIM auction PO and MO can not have Order origin as F-Firm
Test Case 3:Verify that in an AIM auction PO and MO can have Order origin as M-market maker
Test Case 4:Verify that in an AIM auction PO and MO can have Order origin as N-Market Maker Away
Test Case 5:Verify that in an AIM auction PO and MO can have Order origin as B-Broker Dealer
Test Case 6:Verify that Initiator can submit auction responses
Test Case 7:Verify that for a fixed simple AIM auction a percentage response is rejected
Test Case 8:Verify that PO cannot be entered as market order
Test Case 9:Verify that PO trades with booked order and reminder quantity of PO trades with MO and remaining MO is cancelled
Test Case 10:Verify that AIM auctions start at limit price of PO when market maker enters PO as limit order and MO as market order
Test Case 11:Verify that AIM order is rejected when customer order is booked at same price as PO
Test Case 12:Verify that PO trades with auction responses and MO and auction responses are cancelled
Test Case 13:Verify that In AIM AON PO and MO are cancelled when PO is not AON and MO is AON
Test Case 14:Verify that In AIM AON regular auction is started when PO is AON and MO is not AON
Test Case 15:Verify that AIM AON PO trades with customer Order for full quantity and MO is cancelled fully
Test Case 16:Verify that AIM AON PO trades with responses for full quantity MO is cancelled and customer order stays in booked
Test Case 17:Verify that AIM AON PO trades with booked customer order and responses and MO get cancelled. Remaining customer order stays in book
Test Case 18:Verify that AIM AON PO and MO get cancelled when customer Order is with same price and insufficient quantity
Test Case 19:Verify that AIM AON PO and MO trade with each other during On-going auction any incoming tradable orders should be rejected with error code Rejected:Auction in Progress
Test Case 20:Verify that PO trades with BO & MO is non customer when Internelized Guaranteed Percentage is 50 and Remaining BO is booked and MO gets cancelled
Test Case 21:Verify PO trades with MO and BO when MO is non customer and BO remains booked and MO is cancelled. when Internelized Guaranteed Percentage is 50
Test Case 22:Verify that PO trades with BO2 BO1 AR1 MO and AR2 when trading properties Internalized guaranteed percentage 50 and allocation strategies is defined
Test Case 23:Verify that PO trades with MO and MO doesnot cross resting order then AIM auction starting price should be limit price of matched order
Test Case 24:Verify that PO trades with MO when MO crosses a resting non-customer order
Test Case 25:Verify that PO trades with MO and BO trades with AR1 when MO crosses a resting C order and AR crossing BO received
Test Case 26:Verify that PO trades with MO and BO trades with AR1 when MO crosses a resting non-customer order and AR crossing BO received
Test Case 27:Verify that AIM auction cannot be started if MO is of origin F and both PO and MO have same clearing firm
Test Case 28:Verify that AIM auction should not be impacted when users cancels the PO
Test Case 29:Verify that non customer order is booked at same price as MO then PO trades with MO & BO as per Internalized Guaranted Percebtage set.
Test Case 30:Verify that cancel request should not be submitted when users cancels the MO
Test Case 31:Verify that AIM can end prematurely if product state changes Halt in between and auction cannot be continued and Allocation should take place as allocation strategies
Test Case 32:Verify that PO and MO trades with each other at MO price when No booked order and no auction responses
Test Case 33:Verify that AIM can end prematurely if product state changes Suspended in between and auction cannot be continued and Allocation should take place as allocation strategies
Test Case 34:Verify that AIM can end prematurely if product state changes Closed in between and auction cannot be continued and Allocation should take place as allocation strategies
Test Case 35:Verify that PO and MO trades with each other at PO price MO is MKT order when No booked order and no auction responses
Test Case 36:Verify that AIM continues even if the product state changes from Open to Fast
Test Case 37:Verify that PO trades with best available price among Booked order matched order and auction responses
Test Case 38:Verify PO trades with MO when MO crosses resting C order with better penny tick price
Test Case 39:Verify that AIM AON PO and MO trade with each other during On-going auction any FLEX Auction should be rejected with error code Rejected:Auction in Progress
Test Case 40:Verify that AIM AON PO and MO trade with each other during On-going auction any AIM Auction should be rejected with error code Rejected:Auction in Progress
